This sprint introduces a deterministic PLAN artifact that must be approved before any tool execution.

---

## Objective

Replace manual step sequencing with a structured, reviewable plan.

Deliverables:
- Deterministic PLAN schema
- Ordered tool steps with parsed arguments
- Capability scope per step
- No execution until plan approval
- Plan hash logged in audit
- Fail closed on schema violation

---

## Architectural Alignment

Preserves the core enforcement spine:
Orchestrator → AgentLoop → ToolGateway → PolicyEngine → Tool Implementation

No tool is invoked directly from the loop/orchestrator.

---

## PLAN Requirements (Deterministic)

PLAN must:
- Be structured (no free text execution)
- Use explicit ordered steps (step_id 1..N)
- For each step:
  - tool name
  - parsed args object
  - declared capability scope
- Be validated before any execution attempt

Schema violations must deny + audit.

---

## Approval Gate

Execution requires explicit approval:
- If plan not approved → deny execution
- Deny must be auditable

---

## Plan Hash

A stable plan hash must be computed from the validated plan and recorded in audit events:
- PLAN_CREATED (plan_hash, step_count, ...)
- PLAN_APPROVED (plan_hash, approver, ...)
- PLAN_EXECUTION_DENIED (plan_hash, reason, ...)
- PLAN_EXECUTION_STARTED (plan_hash, ...)
- PLAN_EXECUTION_FINISHED (plan_hash, status, ...)

Audit is append-only; events additive only.

---

## Security Boundary

- No free-form execution
- Fail closed on schema violation
- No bypass of ToolGateway/PolicyEngine
- Capability enforcement remains fail-closed per invocation

---

## Definition of Done

- Plan schema + validator implemented and deny-by-default
- Plan hash computed deterministically and logged
- ToolGateway refuses execution without approved plan
- Capability scope is declared per step and enforced
- Tests cover:
  - schema violation denies
  - unapproved plan denies
  - approved plan allows execution path
  - plan hash stable across runs
  - audit events emitted for allow + deny
